{
  "stem": "7739.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 1.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And some locations where the population was greater than maybe a train could accommodate, they used to-- they might have maybe one or two evacuations like this.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They were called [SPEAKING POLISH], or in German Aussiedlung.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they were compared to what you might call an expulsion.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Where the Jewish population was ordered to assemble, in most places in the market square.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] we were told, or we were made to believe, that we were being taken to the Ukraine, where Ukrainian farmers were abandoning their farm, and they needed people to work these farms.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "That's where we were being taken.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I don't know whether people believe this or didn't believe it.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They allowed you to take a certain weight in luggage, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] and that was it.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "The end result is that they rounded up people, they marched them down to the trains-- in our place, maybe I'm going too much ahead of myself.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I don't know.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But up until October 1942, the Jewish people were allowed to live, prior to that, where they lived before.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But in 1941, 1940, 1941, they established a ghetto.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "That means that people in certain streets had to move out into other streets where the ghetto was established.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Consequently, people who lived in the places where they we were not expelled, like made to move, had to share their accommodation with other people from town.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Besides this, in 1940, I believe, they brought in a trainload of people from the city of Plotzk, and a train load of people in the city of Lodz, or Lodz-- left them on the street-- on the train, and the Judenrat-- which was then established-- had to invite these people into the town.",
      "word_count": 54
    }
  ],
